It arises from the very nature of copying, andis by no means con· fined to ancient scribes. Every one who has corrected proofs for his printer will remember how often he has had returned to him such slips as these: vit for viuri, alcides for abelardo, commis- saque dextrae for commissaque dextera dextras, all of which actually were sent in to the editor in the preparation of this edition.
